                <h1>Understanding Earth Day: History and Importance</h1>
                <p>Earth Day, celebrated annually on April 22, began in 1970 as a grassroots environmental movement aimed at raising awareness about pollution and protecting our planet. The founder, Gaylord Nelson, inspired millions to advocate for environmental issues. Today, it unifies communities worldwide in sustainability efforts and climate action.</p>
